[[File:Kuklinski.jpg|thumb|Antoni Kukliński (1997)]]
'''Antoni Kukliński''' (2 June 1927 &ndash; 8 August 2015)<ref>http://nekrologi.wyborcza.pl/0,11,,332091,Antoni-Kukli%C5%84ski-nekrolog.html</ref> was a Polish professor of economics specializing in economic geography and research policy.<ref>{{cite book|title=The individuality of a scholar and advancement of social science : the scholarship of Antoni Kukliński|year=2008|publisher=Rewasz Publishing House|location=Pruszków|isbn=9788389188694|pages=230|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Bi8qLCpcJI8C&printsec=frontcover&hl=pl&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|author=Niżnik, Józef|editor1=Gąsior-Niemiec, Anna |editor2=Niżnik, Józef }}</ref> From 1967 to 1971 he was director of regional research program at [[UNRISD]] (United Nations Research Institute for Social Development). He is a founder of Centre for European Regional and Local Studies (EUROREG)<ref>{{cite web|title=History of EUROREG|url=http://www.euroreg.uw.edu.pl/en/history|accessdate=5 January 2013}}</ref> at the [[University of Warsaw]], [[Poland]].

